          <sec id="Rifampin.Comment2">
            <title>Comment</title>
            <p>Few clinical details are presented by the authors; the point of the case presentation was to attempt to demonstrate a selective interaction of rifampin with the hepatobiliary transport of bilirubin, through competitive inhibition of MRP2 and induction of the MRP3 transporter. The patient likely had Dubin Johnson syndrome, accounting for the benign conjugated hyperbilirubinemia that was exacerbated by rifampin therapy.</p>
          </sec>
